    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nthe new difftool plugin claims \"No difference found\" when diffing two differing folders\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nsetup:\n```\nmkdir a\nmkdir b\n\necho hello      >> a/foo\necho hello      >> b/foo\necho wonderful  >> a/foo\necho world      >> a/foo\necho world!     >> b/foo\n\necho foobar >> b/bar\n```\n\ntry this:\n```\n~/tmp (0)> diff -r a b\nNur in b: bar.\ndiff -r a/foo b/foo\n2,3c2\n< wonderful\n< world\n---\n> world!\n~/tmp (1)> nvim --clean -c \"packadd nvim.difftool\" -d a b # message: \"No difference found\"\n~/tmp (0)>\n```\n\nps: i removed ~/.config/nvim and ~/.local/share/nvim\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nshow the differences in some way, not yet sure how this would look when it works, but definitely don't claim there are \"no differences\"\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1774896198 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndoes it have nvim.difftool?\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.26.1 +pgo +ime +graphemes +toplevel-tag +blur -assertions\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\narchlinux package from \"extra\", the appimage for v0.12 and the one for 0.12.1 also showed the same behaviour",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
